-- Volvo says to take over Nissan Diesel for $1.1 billion
-- 
-- Mon Feb 19, 2007 6:55pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/19/us-nissan-diesel-volvo-idUSTKG00259820070219

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Swedish truck maker Volvo ( VOLVb.ST ) said on Tuesday it will offer 540 yen ($4.51) in cash per share for all the Nissan Diesel Motor Co. Ltd. 7210.T shares it does not own, planning to make the Japanese truck maker a wholly owned unit. 


 The value of the tender offer is 7.5 billion Swedish crowns ($1.1 billion), Volvo said in a statement. Volvo owns 19 percent of Nissan Diesel which has agreed to the offer.